As the In metal covered device showed enhanced UV response, its cyclic dark-to-UV light switching response was obtained, The cyclic dark-to-UV light switching response of ZnO/NR/GQD/In device examined under 360 nm UV light illumination is shown in Fig. 13

                     . The variation of current under cyclic dark-to-UV light illumination at 2 V bias displays the response (T

                        r
                     ) and recovery (T

                        d
                     ) times of 3.5s and 106s, respectively, indicating its quick response to UV light. This fast UV response can be attributed to the effect of the GQDs on the enhancement of the mobility and transport of photogenerated carriers and a reduction in charge recombination [72]. Meanwhile, the slow decay can be attributed to the defect-mediated recombination and absorption of charge carriers at the trap centers.

